  "text": "The combination of these particular factors of the data environment (the type and proliferation of data, and the statistical and technological advances) mean that traditional ways of protecting privacy are less effective in protecting the identities of research subjects. Traditional methods of statistical disclosure control often involve modifying data, through removing information by combining variables or by adding noise to the data. However, these techniques are often ineffective in a real world set-ting where the combination of a number of data sets allows these traditional privacy protections to be circumvented [CITATION_1] .",
